The paper also discusses functional programming and Moggi's monadic point of view, which suggests that cs.PL (Programming Languages) is another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with the semantics of CSP and its operators, which falls under cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also discusses the stable failures model of CSP, which is related to formal methods and verification, making cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the theory of process calculi and its application to CSP, which suggests that cs.THEORY (Theoretical Computer Science) is another likely sub-category.
